('boeing-777-200lr', 'Boeing 777-200LR', 'Boeing', 'The ultra-long-range variant of the 777 family, nicknamed the Worldliner. Capable of connecting virtually any two cities on Earth non-stop, it set the record for the longest non-stop flight by a commercial aircraft.', '2005', '301-440', 17445, 905, 63.7, 64.8, '2x GE90-110B1L', 'Out of Production', 'In 2005, the 777-200LR set the world record for longest non-stop flight, traveling 21,602 km from Hong Kong to London flying eastward over the Pacific.', 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boeing_777', 'Wikipedia', '2026-01-20'),

('boeing-777-9', 'Boeing 777-9', 'Boeing', 'The first variant of the all-new 777X family featuring the worlds largest and most powerful commercial engines and revolutionary folding wingtips. Represents Boeings newest widebody technology with composite wings and advanced aerodynamics.', '2020', '384-426', 13500, 905, 76.7, 71.8, '2x GE9X', 'In Production', 'The 777-9 has folding wingtips that reduce the wingspan from 72m to 65m, allowing it to use the same airport gates as the current 777 despite its larger wings.', 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boeing_777X', 'Wikipedia', '2026-01-20'),

